#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:9
msgid ""
"OpenConnect is a SSL VPN client initially created to support Cisco's "
"AnyConnect SSL VPN. It has since been ported to support the Juniper SSL "
"VPN which is now known as Pulse Connect Secure. Palo Altos Global Protect"
" will also be supported in future and of course the own OpenConnect "
"Server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:16
msgid "Step 1 - Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:18
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`System --> Firmware --> Plugins` and search for "
"**os-openconnect**. Install the plugin as usual, refresh and page and the"
" you'll find the client via :menuselection:`VPN --> OpenConnect`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:24
msgid "Step 2 - Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:26
msgid ""
"The setup of the client is very simple. Just tick **Enable** and fill out"
" **VPN Server**, **Username** and **Password**. Be sure that the FQDN "
"matches the name in the certificate or you will receive an error. Also "
"wildcard certificates can produce errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/openconnect.rst:30
msgid ""
"Once enabled, a new interface will be available for specifying firewall "
"rules; :menuselection:`Firewall --> Rules --> OpenConnect` will appear."
msgstr ""

